comments:
On 9.11.1897 the part in Norfolk 
    was transferred to Parts of Holland, so that thereafter Central Wingland was 
    entirely 
    in Parts of Holland. See also Table 2, notes (a), (b) and (c).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Sutton St. Mary. 
    See also Table 2, note (c).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Sutton St. Mary in 
    Long Sutton Urban District. See also Table 2, note (c).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Sutton St. Mary in 
    Sutton Bridge Urban District. See also Table 2, note (c).

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of Long Sutton, 
    Sutton Bridge and Little Sutton.

That part which until 30.9.1897 formed part of the parish of Central Wingland. 
    See also Table 2, note (a).
